<EFX_PART_I>
<A NAME="FIS_PART_I"></A>
<P ID=PARA315 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	PART I
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA317 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	&nbsp;
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P ID=PARA318 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	ITEM 1.&nbsp; BUSINESS.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA320 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA319 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	COMPANY OVERVIEW
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA322 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA321 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	MeetMe, Inc. (the &#8220;Company,&#8221; &#8220;MeetMe,&#8221; &#8220;us&#8221; or &#8220;we&#8221;) is a location-based social network for meeting new people on mobile platforms, including on iPhone, Android, iPad and other tablets, and the web that facilitates interactions among users and encourages users to connect and chat with each other. MeetMe monetizes through advertising, in-app purchases, and paid subscriptions. MeetMe provides users with access to an expansive, multilingual menu of resources that promote social interaction, information sharing and other topics of interest. The Company offers online marketing capabilities, which enable marketers to display their advertisements in different formats and in different locations. The Company works with its advertisers to maximize the effectiveness of their campaigns by optimizing advertisement formats and placement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA324 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA323 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Just as Facebook has established itself as the social network of friends and family, and LinkedIn as the social network of colleagues and business professionals, MeetMe is creating the social network not of the people you know but of the people you want to know. We believe meeting new people is a basic human need, especially for users aged 18-30, when so many long-lasting relationships are made.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA326 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA325 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe that we have significant growth opportunities as people increasingly use their mobile devices to discover the people around them. Given the importance of establishing connections within a user&#8217;s geographic proximity, we believe it is critical to establish a high density of users within the geographic regions we serve.&nbsp;&nbsp;As the MeetMe network grows and the number of users in a location increases, we believe that users who are seeking to meet new people will incrementally benefit from the quantity of relevant connections.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA328 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA327 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	BUSINESS OVERVIEW
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA330 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA329 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	How We Create Value for Users
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA332 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA331 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The Company believes that it is in the early days of a tremendously large opportunity &#8211; to be the mobile version of the&nbsp;neighborhood&nbsp;bar or coffeehouse, the service of choice among youth to find fun new people to meet and chat with. Our end goal is to be the conduit for connecting people to each other for the over&nbsp;50 million people aged 18-30 in the United States and the more than&nbsp;one billion worldwide. &nbsp;We are unashamedly free, monetizing with our industry-leading mobile monetization infrastructure. As a free, ad-supported service, we are fundamentally different from companies like Match.com, Zoosk, and Spark.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA334 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA333 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The difference between a subscription dating site and MeetMe is the difference between a singles bar and the neighborhood bar. People feel comfortable using MeetMe to make friends, socialize, and chat.&nbsp;In fact, in our internal survey of users conducted in 2015, 89% of those responding said they preferred to start relationships as friends. We believe this&nbsp;comfort level drives higher engagement and retention.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA336 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA335 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe a dramatic shift is underway in the multi-billion dollar&nbsp;dating industry, and that the industry is anchoring towards free with lowered pricing and dramatic investments in free services by existing players. We believe the subscription-dating model is ultimately compromised because it leads to massive churn by its nature.&nbsp;We believe churn&nbsp;ultimately reduces&nbsp;daily active users and restricts user density. We believe the density of users within a geographic area is critical to developing a strong meet-new-people service. Ultimately, the network effect in a meet-new-people service comes down to having nearby, highly relevant users to recommend.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA338 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA337 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	MeetMe has a singular focus on attracting and monetizing the vast majority of its&nbsp;users through superior products. We are not burdened by legacy subscription products, and we believe we are as well positioned as any company to build the global brand for meeting new people.&nbsp;We believe&nbsp;our success will depend in large part, as it does every year, on our ability to continue to execute against an aggressive product pipeline.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA340 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA339 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	More than one million people use MeetMe every day to meet new people in their local communities&nbsp;and throughout&nbsp;the world. These daily active users are increasingly choosing to access MeetMe on their mobile devices, in many cases logging in multiple times per day in order to interact with people they have met on MeetMe.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA342 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA341 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our top priority is to support and grow&nbsp;our dedicated user base by developing innovative ways of bringing people together online. We have historically been able to attract and retain users because we make meeting new people fun and easy. The products we have built for users can be&nbsp;divided into three categories: social networking products, social discovery products, and in-app products available for purchase.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA344 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">

</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA365 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our&nbsp;social discovery products facilitate interactions among members. They are the key vehicles through which we make it fun and easy to meet new people.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA367 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Meet:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; Meet showcases nearby, recently active members (filtered by age and gender preferences) that a member may want to chat with.&nbsp;&nbsp;Because it displays members sorted by proximity to the viewing user, Meet is where MeetMe members go to discover and potentially chat with people geographically closest to them.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Feed:
</B>
	&nbsp; Feed is MeetMe&#8217;s location-based stream communication feature and its most popular application.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unlike the Facebook News Feed,&nbsp;which surfaces content from users&#8217; existing social graphs, our Feed surfaces content from people nearby, thus creating a broader conversation to help users discover new people to meet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Feed can be custom filtered based on age, gender, location or&nbsp;an existing MeetMe friend graph.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P ID=PARA377 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<U>
	In-App Products Available For Purchase
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA379 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<P ID=PARA378 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	MeetMe features an in-app product called Credits, which users can buy directly or earn by completing third-party offers, and several virtual products that users must spend Credits to access or use.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, MeetMe offers a subscription product, MeetMe+, which is currently available only on&nbsp;our mobile apps.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA381 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<B>
	Boost:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; Like Google&#8217;s AdSense, but for people, Boost enables users to purchase placement in some of the most highly trafficked areas of MeetMe,&nbsp;to garner&nbsp;more attention from the community and&nbsp;increase the ability to meet more people faster.&nbsp;
</FONT>

<B>
	Feed Spotlight:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; Feed Spotlight enables users to spend Credits in order to &#8220;pin&#8221; their post to the top of Feed for a limited period of time in order to drive more views, likes, and comments for their content. Spotlighted posts are targeted to a given geographic region and age group.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	MeetMe+:
</B>
	&nbsp; &nbsp;MeetMe+ is a subscription product, available only on&nbsp;our mobile apps, that gives members extra privileges on MeetMe, including additional filtering in Meet, allowances and bonuses&nbsp;of Credits, the ability to see who is viewing your photos, and the ability to suppress mobile advertisements.
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA395 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	How We Create Value for Marketers
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA398 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA397 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe our youthful, highly engaged audience makes MeetMe an attractive publisher for marketers of all sizes, and we focus on providing a wide variety of advertising products that drive our users to engage with brands. During the fourth quarter in 2015, we served over four&nbsp;billion ad impressions each month across our web and mobile applications.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our brand and agency advertising business, also known as direct-sold advertising, is generally powered by companies looking for high-impact ad units and brand engagement from our younger demographic.&nbsp;&nbsp;The majority of our advertising inventory is sold through programmatic media buying.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA400 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA399 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	For part of 2015, we teamed with two companies that were primarily responsible for filling our advertising inventory: Beanstock Media, Inc., or Beanstock, for our website and our mobile applications and Pinsight Media+, Inc., or Pinsight, for our mobile applications. Both companies resold our inventory to numerous individual advertisers and paid us stated contractual rates. We believe this arrangement helped to limit our dependence on one or a few major brands, and minimized the impact of seasonal rate variations typical in the advertising industry. Our agreement with Pinsight terminated at the end of 2014, with a wind-down period that lasted through February 28, 2015. In December of 2014, we expanded our relationship with Beanstock such that beginning on March 1, 2015, Beanstock had the right and obligation to fill certain advertising inventory on our MeetMe mobile apps for iOS and Android, as well as the meetme.com website when accessed using a mobile device and as optimized for mobile devices. On June 2, 2015, we terminated both of our agreements with Beanstock as a result of Beanstock&#8217;s failure to pay amounts owed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA402 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV ID=PGBK26 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<DIV ID=PGFTR26 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<DIV ID=PGNUM26 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	4
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="HEIGHT: 2PX; WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="">
<A NAME="eolPage5"></A>
<DIV ID=PGHDR26 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
</DIV>
<P ID=PARA26.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA401 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<U>
	Social Theater
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA404 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA403 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our Social Theater product enables publishers to incentivize their users to take certain actions in exchange for the hosting platform&#8217;s virtual currency.&nbsp;&nbsp;Social Theater advertising runs not only on MeetMe, where our users can watch videos and otherwise engage with brands in exchange for Credits, but also on social games and applications across other social networks, including Facebook.&nbsp;&nbsp;Social Theater can also be used by marketers to drive video views, application installs, and&nbsp;&#8220;likes&#8221; and &#8220;shares&#8221; on Facebook, Twitter, and other social platforms. When a Social Theater campaign is distributed outside of MeetMe on a different platform we consider it &#8220;Cross-Platform Revenues.&#8221;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA406 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA405 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Our Strategy
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA408 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA407 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe we are well positioned to pioneer the next category of social networking: social discovery. Our strategy for 2016 and beyond is aimed at continued growth and engagement of our active user base and improving the rate at which we monetize our active users, especially on mobile.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA410 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA409 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Key elements of our strategy include:
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA412 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE ID=MTAB413 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 25PT">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA414 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA415 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Build Great Products to Acquire, Engage, and Thrill Users:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; Our core focus&nbsp;is to create innovative social experiences that help our users meet new people in their local communities or&nbsp;throughout the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;We&nbsp;plan on continuing&nbsp;to invest in improving our core platform as technology advances and in devising new ways of transforming the traditional experience of friendship-making as that activity increasingly moves online.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Offer Innovative and Engaging Ad Products for Marketers:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; We consider it critical to continue improving our advertising products to create more value for our marketers, attract new customers, and display targeted advertisements that are more relevant for our users. We pursue these goals through a combination of internal innovation and rapid integration of advertising solutions that have been successful in the marketplace.

<B>
	Expand Our Reach Internationally:
</B>
	&nbsp;&nbsp; There are over one billion people aged 18-30 worldwide,&nbsp;of which&nbsp;approximately 50&nbsp;million reside in the United States, where our traffic has historically been centered.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2013, we internationalized the platform and launched in twelve languages other than English, laying the foundation for significant future growth in other geographies. In 2015, some of our fastest growing audiences were international, including in countries such as Turkey, Italy, India, and elsewhere. For more information, see notes to consolidated financial statements&#8212;

<P ID=PARA426 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT 0PT 0PT 49PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA429 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA428 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Operating Metrics
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA431 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA430 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We measure website and application activity in terms of monthly active users (&#8220;MAUs&#8221;) and daily active users (&#8220;DAUs&#8221;). We define MAU as a registered user of one of our platforms who has logged in and visited within the last month of measurement. We define DAU as a registered user of one of our platforms who has logged in and visited within the day of measurement. For the quarters ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, the total MeetMe MAUs were approximately 4.97 million, 4.98 million and 5.54 million, respectively, and total MeetMe DAUs were approximately 1.19 million, 1.09 million and 1.10 million, respectively. MeetMe visits were approximately 1.97 billion, 1.67 billion and 0.93 billion, respectively, for the quarters ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013. The aggregate total of registered users on MeetMe platforms were approximately 136 million, 109 million and 82 million for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA432 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV ID=PGNUM27 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	5
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="HEIGHT: 2PX; WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="">
<A NAME="eolPage6"></A>
<DIV ID=PGHDR27 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
</DIV>
<P ID=PARA27.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA499 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Trends in Our Metrics
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA501 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA500 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	In addition to MAUs and DAUs, we measure activity on&nbsp;MeetMe in terms of average revenue per user (&#8220;ARPU&#8221;) and average daily&nbsp;revenue per daily active user (&#8220;ARPDAU&#8221;).&nbsp; We define ARPU as the quarterly average revenue per MAU. We define ARPDAU as the average quarterly revenue per DAU.&nbsp;We define mobile MAU as a user who accessed our sites by a one of our mobile applications or by the mobile optimized version of our website, whether on a mobile phone or tablet during the month of measurement. We define a mobile DAU as a user who accessed our sites by one of our mobile applications or by the mobile optimized version of our website, whether on a mobile phone or tablet during the day of measurement.&nbsp;Visits represent the number of times during the measurement period that users came to the website or mobile applications for distinct sessions.&nbsp;&nbsp;A page view is a page that a user views during a visit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA503 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA502 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	In the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, MeetMe averaged 4.06 million mobile MAUs and 4.97 million total MAUs on average, as compared to 3.09 million mobile MAUs and 4.98 million total MAUs on average in the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, a net increase of 0.97 million or 31% for mobile MAUs, and a net decrease of 11,000 or 0.2% for total MeetMe MAUs. Mobile DAUs were 1.1 million for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, a 20% increase, from 923,000 in the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. For the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, MeetMe averaged 1.19 million total DAUs, as compared to 1.09 million total DAUs on average for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014, a net increase of approximately 100,000 total DAUs, or 9%.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA505 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA504 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe the shift of our audience from web to mobile is an important driver of our business. Although decreasing web traffic has resulted in&nbsp;declining web revenue, we have successfully increased our mobile revenue by 126%&nbsp;and our mobile ARPDAU by 89% to $17.2 million and $0.169, respectively, for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 from $7.6 million and $0.09, respectively, for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our mobile revenue increased by 49%&nbsp;and our mobile ARPDAU by 29% to $7.6 million and $0.09, respectively, for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 from $5.1 million and $0.07, respectively, for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2013. We believe our ability to continue to grow our mobile audience and our mobile monetization at a faster pace than the decline in our web revenue will impact the performance of our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA507 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

	&nbsp;
</P>

<P ID=PARA30.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA510 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	In the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, MeetMe earned an average of $0.87 ARPU on the web and $4.22 in ARPU in our mobile applications, as compared to $1.03 in web ARPU and $2.46 in mobile ARPU for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. In the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, MeetMe earned an average of $0.106 in web ARPDAU and $0.169 in mobile ARPDAU, as compared to $0.133 in web ARPDAU and $0.09 in mobile ARPDAU for the quarter ended December&nbsp;31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA513 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA519 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA29.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA520 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA523 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA522 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We are continually developing new products, as well as optimizing our existing platform and feature set in order to meet the evolving needs of our user base and&nbsp;advertising partners.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA525 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA524 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We develop most of our software internally.&nbsp;&nbsp;We will, however, purchase technology and license intellectual property rights where it is strategically important, operationally compatible, or&nbsp;economically advantageous.&nbsp;&nbsp;For instance, we partner with third parties to further our internationalization efforts as we look to bring additional languages into our existing platforms.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are not materially dependent upon licenses and other agreements with third parties relating to product development.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA527 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA526 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our technology team of approximately 59 people consists of our product development and engineering team, our database administration team, our quality assurance team and our network system operators.&nbsp;&nbsp;These teams are responsible for feature enhancements and general maintenance across all of our platforms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our technology team is headquartered in New Hope, Pennsylvania.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA529 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV ID=PGBK35 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; MARGIN-LEFT: 0PT; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<DIV ID=PGFTR35 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
<DIV ID=PGNUM35 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: CENTER">
	7&nbsp;
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="HEIGHT: 2PX; WIDTH: 100%; PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS; COLOR: #000000" NOSHADE="">
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<DIV ID=PGHDR35 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
</DIV>
<P ID=PARA35.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA528 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	SALES AND MARKETING
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA531 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA530 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Historically,&nbsp;we have grown our&nbsp;user base in large part through organic, viral channels.&nbsp;&nbsp;By encouraging members to invite their friends to join MeetMe and to share their activity across other external platforms, including Facebook and Twitter, and by&nbsp;providing&nbsp;members with easy-to-use tools, we believe we have&nbsp;successfully grown&nbsp;our user base while minimizing marketing costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We focus primarily on creating a truly differentiated experience and compelling value proposition for new users in our markets and developing the technologies needed to facilitate their word-of-mouth marketing on our behalf in order to attract and retain new members.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA533 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P ID=PARA532 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our paid customer acquisition strategy continues to focus on acquiring users in new geographies where the active user base on the core MeetMe platform had previously been small in comparison to our user base in the United States and Canada.&nbsp;We spent $3.3 million, $2.0 million and $2.5 million on&nbsp;paid direct user acquisition in 2015, 2014 and 2013, or 5.9%, 4.5% and 6.2% of our total revenue, respectively.&nbsp;We plan to increase this spend rate in 2016 to 10% of revenue, as we believe this well lead to higher mobile ARPU.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA535 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA534 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	SALES AND OPERATIONS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA537 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA536 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our advertising sales and operations team is comprised of 12 full-time employees in the United States and covers major brand agencies, direct response and cost-per-action engagement advertisers, advertising networks, and mobile agencies. Our advertising operations are headquartered in New Hope, Pennsylvania, with additional offices in New York, New York and Los Angeles, California.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA539 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA538 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our operations and member services team consists of 20 full-time employees,&nbsp;8 part-time employees, and 20 contractors split between Delhi and Bangalore, India. This team is responsible for reviewing images and other user-generated content, investigating and responding to member abuse reports, and providing general customer support.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA541 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our intellectual property includes trademarks related to our brands, products, and services; copyrights in software and creative content; trade secrets; domain names; and other intellectual property rights and licenses of various kinds.&nbsp;&nbsp;We seek to protect our intellectual property through copyright, trade secret, trademark and other laws of the U.S. and other countries, and through contractual provisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA545 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<P ID=PARA547 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<P ID=PARA548 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We operate at the forefront of a nascent segment (social discovery) of a broader sector that is still being defined (social networking). As such, we face significant competition in every aspect of our business, both from established companies whose products help users meet new people, or are evolving to do so, and from smaller but well-funded startups that can quickly gain attention and compete with us for users. Examples of services that compete with us for users and advertiser interest include, but are not limited to:
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA580 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

	&nbsp;

<P ID=PARA579 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	As of March 4, 2016, we employed approximately&nbsp;104 full time and&nbsp;8 part time employees in the United States. Our future success is substantially dependent on the performance of our senior management and key technical personnel, as well as our continuing ability to attract, maintain the caliber of, and retain highly qualified technical and managerial personnel.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional information regarding certain risks related to our employees is included in Part I, Item 1A &#8220;Risk Factors&#8221; of this report and is incorporated herein by reference.
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA582 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<P ID=PARA581 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	GOVERNMENT REGULATION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA584 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA583 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	In the United States, advertising and promotional information presented to visitors on our mobile applications and website&nbsp;and our other marketing activities are subject to federal and state consumer protection laws that regulate unfair and deceptive practices. There are a variety of state and federal restrictions on the marketing activities conducted by email, or over the Internet, including U.S. federal and state privacy laws and the Telephone Consumer Protection Act of 1991, or the TCPA,&nbsp;the Controlling the Assault of Non-Solicited Pornography and Marketing Act of 2001, or the CAN-SPAM Act. We may also be subject to laws in the various other countries in which we operate.&nbsp;&nbsp;The rules and regulations are complex and may be subject to different interpretations by courts or other governmental authorities. We&nbsp;may unintentionally violate such laws, such laws may be modified, and new laws may be enacted in the future. Any such developments (or developments stemming from enactment or modification of other laws) or the failure to anticipate accurately the application or interpretation of these laws could create liability to us, result in adverse publicity, and negatively affect our businesses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional information regarding certain risks related to government regulations is included in Part I, Item 1A, &#8220;Risk Factors&#8221; of this report.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA586 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	CORPORATE HISTORY
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA588 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA587 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	MeetMe was incorporated in Nevada in June 1997, and merged with Insider Guides, Inc., doing business as myYearbook.com, on November 10, 2011. On December 6, 2011, the Company changed its legal domicile to Delaware.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company is a social media technology company that owns and operates the MeetMe mobile applications and meetme.com. Effective June 1, 2012, the Company changed its name from Quepasa Corporation to MeetMe, Inc. and completed its transition to meetme.com in the fourth quarter of 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA590 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

	Our executive offices and principal facilities are located at 100 Union Square Drive, New Hope, Pennsylvania, 18938.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our telephone number is (215) 862-1162.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our corporate website is www.meetmecorp.com.&nbsp;&nbsp;Investors can obtain copies of our SEC filings from our corporate website free of charge, as well as from the SEC website, www.sec.gov.&nbsp;&nbsp;The information contained on our corporate website and the SEC&nbsp;website is not incorporated herein.
</FONT>

</P>
<P ID=PARA593 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">

<EFX_RISK_FACTORS>
<A NAME="FIS_RISK_FACTORS"></A>
<P ID=PARA597 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	ITEM 1A.&nbsp;&nbsp;RISK FACTORS.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA599 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA598 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Investing in our common stock involves a high degree of risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;You should consider carefully the risks and uncertainties described below, together with all of the other information in this report, including the consolidated financial statements and the related notes included elsewhere in this report, before deciding whether to invest in shares of our common stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;The risks and uncertainties described below are not the only ones we face.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional risks and uncertainties that we are unaware of, or that we currently believe are not material may also become important factors that adversely affect our business.&nbsp;&nbsp;If any of the following risks actually occurs, our business, financial condition, results of operations, and future prospects could be materially and adversely affected.&nbsp;&nbsp;In that event, the market price of our common stock could decline, and you could lose part or all of your investment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA601 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

<U>
<B>
	Risk Related to Our Business
</B>
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA603 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<B>
	If we cannot increase our&nbsp;daily and monthly active users&nbsp;and increase their engagement on MeetMe, our future operating results may decline.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We offer applications that are free to use, with only a small percentage of our users paying for virtual goods.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our financial performance has been and will continue to be significantly determined by our success in adding, retaining, and engaging active users. We must continue to add new members to our user base and retain existing members by offering new and engaging features and products in order to attract advertising investment and generate revenue from the sale of in-app products.&nbsp;&nbsp;The challenges we face include, among other things, our ability to:

<DIV ID=PGHDR37 STYLE="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT">
	&nbsp;
</DIV>
</DIV>
<P ID=PARA37.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA656 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	If we fail to retain existing users or add new users, or if our users decrease their level of engagement, our revenue, financial results, and business may be significantly harmed.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA659 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA658 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The size of our user base and our users&#8217; level of engagement are critical to our success.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our financial performance is significantly affected by our success in adding, retaining, and engaging active users.&nbsp;&nbsp;If people do not perceive our products to be useful, reliable, and trustworthy, we may not be able to attract or retain users or otherwise maintain or increase the frequency and duration of their engagement.&nbsp;&nbsp;A number of other social networking companies that achieved early popularity have since seen their active user bases or levels of engagement decline, in some cases precipitously.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is no guarantee that we will not experience a similar erosion of our active user base or engagement levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;A decrease in user retention, growth, or engagement could render us less attractive to advertisers, which may have a material and adverse impact on our revenue, business, financial condition, and results of operations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any number of factors could potentially negatively affect user retention, growth, and engagement, including if we fail to:
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA661 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	We believe&nbsp;the number of our registered users is higher than the number of actual users.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA700 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA699 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We believe&nbsp;the number of our registered users is higher than the number of actual users because some members may have multiple registrations, other members may have died or may have become incapacitated, and others may have registered under fictitious names.&nbsp;&nbsp;Members also terminate their memberships and delete their profiles.&nbsp; Given the challenges inherent in identifying these accounts, we do not have a reliable system to accurately identify the number of our&nbsp;active&nbsp;members.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA702 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA701 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	If our users do not interact with each other or our viral marketing strategy fails, our ability to attract new users&nbsp;may suffer and our revenue&nbsp;may decrease.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA704 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA703 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The&nbsp;majority of our users do not visit&nbsp;MeetMe frequently and spend a limited amount of time when they do visit.&nbsp;The majority of our page views are generated by a minority of our users.&nbsp;If we are unable to encourage our users to interact more frequently and to increase the amount of user generated content they provide, our ability to attract new users and our financial results&nbsp;may suffer.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, part of our success depends on our users interacting with our&nbsp;products and contributing to our viral advertising platform (Social Theater).&nbsp;&nbsp;If our Social Theater platform is unsuccessful and our&nbsp;users do not&nbsp;participate in Social Theater campaigns,&nbsp;our operating results could suffer.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA706 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">

<P ID=PARA35.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">

<P ID=PARA705 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	We generate the majority of our revenue from advertising.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we incur a loss of advertisers, or a reduction in spending by advertisers, our revenue could substantially decline, resulting in significant operating losses and negatively&nbsp;impacting our cash flows.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA708 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

<P ID=PARA707 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We generate most of our revenue from parties advertising on our platform.&nbsp;&nbsp;As is common in the industry, our advertisers typically do not have long-term advertising commitments with us.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many of our advertisers spend only a relatively small portion of their overall advertising budget with us.&nbsp;&nbsp;Advertisers will not continue to do business with us, or they will reduce the prices they are willing to pay to advertise with us, if we do not deliver advertising and other commercial content in an effective manner, or if they do not believe that their investment in advertising with us will generate a competitive return relative to other alternatives.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our advertising revenue could be adversely affected by a number of other factors, including:
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
</TD>

	The occurrence of any of these or other factors could result in a reduction in demand for our advertising and other commercial content, which could reduce the prices we receive for our advertising and other commercial content, or cause advertisers to stop advertising with us altogether.&nbsp;&nbsp;In turn, we could incur a substantial decline in revenue, increased operating losses, and a negative impact on cash flows.
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA761 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">

<P ID=PARA32 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	We have terminated our agreements with our&nbsp;advertising partner and&nbsp;may not be able to collect amounts due.
</B>
	&nbsp; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA33 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA34 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	On June 2, 2015, we terminated two agreements with Beanstock relating to our advertising inventory on web and mobile: the Web Agreement and the Mobile Agreement. We terminated both agreements for non-payment, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	in the third quarter of 2015, we wrote-off the accounts receivable balance under the agreements of approximately $5.7 million as uncollectible. We have filed suit against Beanstock and its guarantor, Adaptive Medias, Inc., and we intend to pursue all available remedies to collect amounts due to us, including liquidated damages under the Mobile Agreement. We cannot guarantee if, when or how much outstanding will be paid to us. We also do not know the amount of time and effort that will be required from management to collect these amounts. For a description of the litigation, see &#8220;Item 3 &#8211; Legal Proceedings.&#8221;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
	&nbsp;

<P ID=PARA769 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
<I>
	&nbsp;
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA770 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	We fill our advertising inventory internally, without the use an external advertising partner as in the past, and
</B>
	&nbsp;
<B>
	if we fail to maintain and expand our base of advertisers, our revenue and our business could be harmed.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA36.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA772 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our ability to grow our business depends in part on our ability to maintain and expand our advertiser base. To do so, we must ensure that existing and prospective advertisers know that our advertising products offer a material benefit and can generate a competitive return relative to other alternatives, including online, mobile and traditional advertising platforms. Advertisers may not continue to do business with us, or they may reduce the prices they are willing to pay to advertise with us, if we do not deliver ads in an effective manner, or if they do not believe that their investment in advertising with us will generate competitive returns. Our ability to do so depends on&nbsp;factors&nbsp;including:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 12PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA775 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE ID=MTAB776 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 25PT">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA777 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA778 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Competitiveness of Our Products.&nbsp;We must deliver ads in an effective manner and provide accurate analytics and measurement solutions that demonstrate the value of our advertising products compared to those of our competitors. Similarly, if the pricing of our advertising products does not compare favorably to those of our competitors, advertisers may reduce their advertising with us or choose not to advertise with us at all.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P ID=PARA780 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE ID=MTAB781 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 25PT">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA782 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA783 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Traffic Quality.&nbsp;The success of our advertising program depends on delivering positive results to our advertising customers. Low-quality or invalid traffic, such as robots, spiders and the mechanical automation of clicking, may be detrimental to our relationships with advertisers and could adversely affect our advertising pricing and revenue. If we fail to detect and prevent click fraud or other invalid clicks on ads, the affected advertisers may experience or perceive a reduced return on their investments, which could lead to dissatisfaction with our products, refusals to pay, refund demands or withdrawal of future business.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P ID=PARA785 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

<TABLE ID=MTAB786 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>

	&nbsp;

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>

</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA788 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Perception of Our Platform.&nbsp;Our ability to compete effectively for advertiser budgets depends on our reputation and perceptions regarding our platform.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P ID=PARA790 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<TABLE ID=MTAB791 STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0PX" CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 25PT">
	&nbsp;
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH: 24PT; VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA792 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&#9679;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN: TOP">
<P ID=PARA793 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Macroeconomic Conditions.&nbsp;Adverse macroeconomic conditions can have a negative impact on the demand for advertising, particularly with respect to online advertising products. Advertisers may have limited advertising budgets and may view online advertising as lower priority than offline advertising.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<P ID=PARA794 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT 0PT 0PT 36PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 12PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA795 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	As is typical in our industry, our advertisers generally do not have long-term obligations to purchase our products. Their decisions to renew depend on the degree of satisfaction with our products as well as a number of&nbsp;factors&nbsp;that are outside of our control. As a result, we may experience attrition in our advertisers in the ordinary course of business resulting from several&nbsp;factors, including losses to competitors or declining advertising budgets. The occurrence of any of these or other&nbsp;factors&nbsp;could result in a reduction in demand for our ads, which may reduce the prices we receive for our ads, either of which would negatively affect our revenue and operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA796 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 12PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA797 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	If we cannot effectively monetize our mobile products, we may not be able to successfully grow our business.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA799 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA798 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The shift of our audience from web to mobile may be disruptive to our business and operating results.&nbsp;As our users shift from web to mobile access, web page views have decreased.&nbsp; Decreasing web traffic&nbsp;contributes to&nbsp;declining web revenue.&nbsp; Our business faces the challenge of ramping up mobile monetization to offset declining web revenues as users continue to increase their mobile access.&nbsp;&nbsp;The transition in our user access could impact revenue in the short-term and medium-term as mobile monetization continues to mature slowly.&nbsp;&nbsp;Accordingly, as users increasingly access MeetMe mobile products as a substitute for using personal computers, if personal computer usage continues to be phased out by the popularity of smart phones and tablets, and if we are unable to successfully implement monetization strategies for our mobile users, our revenue and financial results could be negatively affected.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA801 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA800 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Because we face significant competition from other social networks and companies with greater resources, we may not be able to compete effectively.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA803 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA802 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We face significant competition from other companies that seek to connect members online.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our competitors are other companies providing portal and online community services, such as Facebook, Google, Tagged, Badoo, PlentyOfFish, Skout, and Okcupid.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many of our competitors have greater resources, more established reputations, a broader range of content and products and services, longer operating histories, and more established relationships with their users than we do.&nbsp;They can use their experience and resources against us in a variety of competitive ways, including developing ways to attract and maintain users.&nbsp; These factors may allow our competitors to respond more effectively than us to new or emerging technologies and changes in market requirements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Our competitors may develop products, features, or services that are similar to ours or that achieve greater market acceptance, may undertake more far-reaching and successful efforts at developing new services or marketing campaigns, or may adopt more aggressive pricing policies. Some of our competitors may enjoy better competitive positions in certain geographical regions or within certain user demographics that we currently serve or may serve in the future. These advantages could enable these competitors to offer products that are more appealing to users and potential users than our products or to respond more quickly and/or cost-effectively than us to new or changing opportunities. In addition, within the industry generally, costs for users to switch between products are low, and users have a propensity to try new approaches to connecting with people. As a result, new products, entrants and business models are likely to continue to emerge. It is possible that a new product could gain rapid scale at the expense of existing brands through harnessing a new technology or distribution channel, creating a new approach to connecting people or some other means.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA805 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
<P ID=PARA873 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	Because we face competition from traditional media companies, we may not be included in the advertising budgets of large advertisers, which could harm our operating results.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA876 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA875 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Major brand and network advertising drives most of our revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;We rely primarily on cost per thousand (&#8220;CPM&#8221;) advertising, where&nbsp;the price&nbsp;for advertising is based&nbsp;on the number of users who view it.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to mobile application developers and Internet companies, we face competition from companies that offer traditional media advertising opportunities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most large advertisers have set advertising budgets, a portion of which is allocated to Internet and mobile advertising.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect that large advertisers will continue to increase their advertising efforts on the Internet and mobile devices.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we fail to convince these companies to spend a portion of their advertising budgets on social media and specifically with us, however, our operating results could be harmed.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA878 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA877 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	An increasing number of individuals are using devices other than personal computers to access the Internet.&nbsp;&nbsp;If versions of our applications developed for these devices do not gain widespread adoption, or do not function as intended, our business could be adversely affected.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA880 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA879 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The number of people who access the Internet through devices other than personal computers, including smart phones, cell phones and handheld tablets, has increased dramatically in the past few years and is projected to continue to increase.&nbsp;&nbsp; We have launched a MeetMe mobile application for Android smart phones, iPhones and iPads.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are dependent on interoperability with popular mobile operating systems that we do not control, such as Android and iOS, and any changes in such systems that degrade our platform&#8217;s functionality or give preferential treatment to competitive services could adversely affect our mobile application usage.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each device manufacturer or platform provider may establish unique or restrictive terms and conditions for developers on such devices or platforms, and our applications may not work well or be viewable on these devices as a result.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA28.1 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P ID=PARA28.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA882 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	We rely on the Apple App Store and the Google Play Store to distribute our mobile applications. Our business will suffer if we are unable to maintain a good relationship with
</B>
<B>
	Apple and Google,
</B>
<B>
	if their terms and conditions or pricing change to our detriment, if we violate, or
</B>
<B>
	either
</B>
<B>
	believes that we have violated,
</B>
<B>
	its
</B>
<B>
	terms and conditions
</B>
<B>
	,
</B>
<B>
	or if
</B>
<B>
	either
</B>
<B>
	of these platforms are unavailable for a prolonged period of time.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA38.2 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA884 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	The Apple App Store and the Google Play Store&nbsp;are our primary distribution, marketing, promotion and payment platforms for our apps. Any deterioration in our relationship with Google or Apple would harm our business and adversely affect the value of our stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA885 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 24PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA886 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We are subject to these platforms&#8217; standard terms and conditions for application developers, which govern the promotion, distribution and operation of applications. These platforms have policies governing, for example, use of user data, personal and sensitive information, and advertising IDs, as well as ones relating to advertising (including deceptive, disruptive and inappropriate ads) and interference with application and device functionality. If we violate, or if a platform provider believes we have violated, these terms and conditions, the particular platform provider may discontinue or limit our access to that platform, which could prevent us from satisfying our contractual obligations to our mobile customers. Our business could also be harmed if a platform provider modifies its current terms of service or other policies, including fees, in a manner adverse to us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA887 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 24PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA888 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We also rely on the continued operation and availability of these third-party platforms. In the past, platforms have been unavailable for short periods of time. On more than one occasion, for example, Apple has&nbsp;rejected our applications because of user generated content and other concerns. In response we devoted additional resources to image review, and changed some of our content allowance policies.&nbsp;&nbsp;If this recurs on a prolonged or frequent basis, or other similar issues arise that impact users&#8217; ability to download or use our mobile event applications, we may owe some of our customers rebates, which would increase our expenses and lower our gross margins. Our revenue, operating results or brands could also suffer harm. Furthermore, any material change or deterioration in our relationship with these platform providers could harm our business.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA889 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: LEFT; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25; TEXT-INDENT: 24PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA890 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PX; MARGIN-TOP: 0PX; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Furthermore, if Google or Apple loses its market position or otherwise falls out of favor with users, we would need to identify alternative channels for marketing, promoting and distributing our apps, which would consume substantial resources and may not be effective. In addition, Google and Apple have broad discretion to change their terms of service and other policies with respect to us and other developers, and those changes may be unfavorable to us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA892 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA891 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	If the Apple &#8220;App Store&#8221; or &#8220;Google Play&#8221; changes its search and rating algorithms, it could affect our ability to acquire new mobile members.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA894 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA893 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	Our iPhone and Android applications rank near the top of the &#8220;Free Social&#8221; categories and near the top of many key search terms.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, Apple and Google have changed their rating and search algorithms in the past without notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;Future changes to the rating and search algorithms by Apple or Google could impact our rating and search results, leading to a drop in new mobile application downloads, which could cause our business and operating results to suffer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA896 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P ID=PARA895 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
<B>
	If we are unable to continue to develop successful applications for mobile platforms and standalone mobile applications, our growth prospects could suffer.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ID=PARA898 STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0PT; MARGIN-TOP: 0PT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">

<P ID=PARA897 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We have offered applications for mobile platforms since May 2010.&nbsp;We expect to continue to devote substantial resources to the development of mobile applications, but there can be no assurances that we will continue to succeed in developing applications that appeal to users or advertisers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We may encounter difficulty in attracting leading advertisers to our mobile applications.&nbsp; We may also face challenges working with wireless carriers, mobile platform providers and other mobile communications partners.&nbsp;&nbsp;Finally, we may face challenges converting mobile users into users that pay for in-app products.&nbsp;&nbsp;These and other uncertainties make it difficult to know whether we will continue to succeed in developing commercially viable applications for mobile platforms.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we do not succeed in doing so, our growth prospects could suffer.
</FONT>
</P>

<P ID=PARA983 STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN: JUSTIFY; MARGIN: 0PT; LINE-HEIGHT: 1.25">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE: 10PT; FONT-FAMILY: TIMES NEW ROMAN, TIMES, SERIF">
	We conduct our business in countries outside of&nbsp;the United States and depend on payment gateways that are not as well developed as those in the United States, where most people have credit cards or bank debit cards to use in paying for virtual goods, products, and services.&nbsp;&nbsp;Users in some countries in which we operate do not always have access to credit and debit cards and other payment methods common in the United States.&nbsp;&nbsp;If we are unable to implement payment gateways that provide our members with&nbsp;the ability to pay for goods, products and services easily, our future results could be adversely affected.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, our inability to collect and receive payments from these other sources could have an adverse effect on our business and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>

	&nbsp;
</DIV>
